parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature brake rotor failure can lead to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and potentially cause accidents, especially in emergency braking situations.
symptoms: Warped or excessively worn brake rotors
vibrations or pulsations when braking
squealing or grinding noises when applying the brakes
and wobbling or shaking of the steering wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rear brake caliper failure can cause the brakes to stick or drag, leading to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Rear brake calipers sticking or staying on as if the parking brake was engaged
grinding or squealing noises when applying the brakes
and vibrations or pulsations when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A design flaw in the brake system can lead to premature wear of brake components, reduced braking performance, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Excessive wear on brake pads and rotors
vibrations or pulsations when braking
and wobbling or shaking of the steering wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to shut down without warning, resulting in loss of acceleration, brakes, and steering, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts down without warning
all dashboard lights illuminate
unknown fumes fill the vehicle cabin
the vehicle decreases in speed without warning
windshield wipers and lights on the instrument panel turn on unexpectedly
gauges on the instrument panel fail and start to blink on and off
fuel gauge fluctuates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the instrument panel can cause distractions while driving, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Gauges on the instrument panel fail and start to blink on and off
fuel gauge fluctuates
windshield wipers and lights on the instrument panel turn on unexpectedly
chimes go off as if a door is open
driver's seat starts sliding back and forth as if being adjusted.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system failure can cause a vehicle fire, which can result in total loss of the vehicle and potentially cause injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle catches fire
windshield wipers are turned on
lights on the instrument panel are illuminated
fire originates under the hood.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to shut down, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts down while driving
all lights on the instrumental panel illuminate
the vehicle can be restarted after turning it off for a few minutes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can lead to reduced braking performance, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The ABS light illuminates on the dashboard
the vehicle experiences issues with braking performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioning condenser can cause water to accumulate on the floor, leading to potential electrical issues and safety hazards.
symptoms: Water accumulates on the floor
the air conditioning system does not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The battery drain can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to loss of control and potential accidents. In severe cases, it can cause an electrical fire, resulting in damage to the vehicle and potential harm to occupants.
symptoms: The battery goes dead
the vehicle stalls
the radio or temperature gauge remains on even when the vehicle is turned off
the vehicle catches on fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates without warning
the brakes do not respond or are unable to slow the vehicle down
the vehicle becomes stuck in gear
the vehicle surges or continues to accelerate even after releasing the accelerator pedal.
